1. Clone, or download, the repository in your local machine.

2. Navigate to the project directory, and compile the program using the command : cc project.c -o <executable> 

3. You may change the source image by putting an image of your choice in the source_images folder.

4. Run the executable using the command ./<executable> <source image name>

5. Enter the grid size of your choice, using powers of 2 (2,4,8 and so on)

6. The output is the image named output.pgm in the project directory.


